Hibernate mapping is one of the key features of Hibernate.
By using mapping, we can establish connection between two or more tables.
We can establish either unidirectional or bidirectional relationship.

Relationships can be established between entities as:
One to One
One to Many
Many to One
Many to Many

Uni-directional mapping
 
If the relationship is defined inside any one of the entities, then it is called Uni-directional mapping.
Only one entity knows about the relationship, the other entity has no reference back.
The mapping exists in one direction only.
 
Bi-directional mapping
 
If the relationship is defined inside both the entities, then it is called as Bi-directional mapping.
Both entities know about each other.
The mapping/relationship exists in both directions.

